    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "# Problem\n\nCurrently the oldtests are run with a combination of a makefiles and shell scripts such as `ci/*.sh`, `src/nvim/testdir/Makefile` and `src/nvim/testdir/runnvim.sh`. The annoying thing is that this isn't very cross-platform. From my understanding, running the oldtests on Windows requires msys2, which requires its own setup and has its own quirks. For example, the path to msys2 has changed in the latest Windows runner in GitHub Actions, which makes a simple version bump impossible like with Linux and Mac.\n\n# Proposal\n\nRewrite the oldtest \"engine\" (i.e. the makefile and the shell scripts) in ctest. We already use cmake, so this isn't a new requirement. It will also allow us to drop msys2 and other workarounds and only have a single implementation that shouldn't require any external workarounds.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
